# ISP Truth Tester

A small Python tool for Raspberry Pi (or any Linux box) that monitors your internet connection over time. It runs **ping tests** frequently and **speed tests** periodically, logs everything to text and JSON, and produces a self-contained HTML report with min / avg / max stats and charts.

## Features

- Configurable session length (**1–24 hours**)
- Ping latency checks every 30 seconds (configurable)
- Speed tests every 10 minutes (configurable) via [speedtest-cli](https://github.com/sivel/speedtest-cli)
- Text log + JSON data + HTML dashboard
- **Graceful shutdown** — press `Ctrl+C` or send `SIGTERM` and all collected data is saved and the report is generated
- Exits silently when finished (use `--verbose` for progress messages)

## Quick start (Raspberry Pi)

```bash
# Clone and install
cd ISP_truth_tester
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .

# Run a 2-hour monitoring session
isp-truth-tester run --duration 2

# Open the report (path printed with --verbose, or look in results/)
# results/session_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS_report.html
```

## Usage

```bash
# Required: how long to run (1–24 hours)
isp-truth-tester run --duration 4

# Customize intervals and targets
isp-truth-tester run --duration 8 \
  --ping-interval 30 \
  --speed-interval 600 \
  --targets 1.1.1.1 8.8.8.8 \
  --output-dir ./results

# Show progress while running
isp-truth-tester run --duration 1 --verbose

# Regenerate HTML from saved JSON
isp-truth-tester report results/session_20250621_120000.json
```

You can also run it as a module:

```bash
python -m isp_truth_tester run --duration 2
```

## Output files

Each session creates three files in the output directory:

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `session_*.log` | Human-readable text log |
| `session_*.json` | Structured data (for re-reporting or analysis) |
| `session_*_report.html` | Dashboard with stats and charts — open in any browser |

## Stopping early

If you cancel mid-run (`Ctrl+C`, `kill`, etc.), the tool saves all data collected so far and still writes the HTML report. The report will show **Stopped early** instead of **Completed**.

## Requirements

- Python 3.10+
- `ping` available on PATH (standard on Raspberry Pi OS)
- Network access for speed tests

## systemd example (optional)

Run an 8-hour session on boot:

```ini
[Unit]
Description=ISP Truth Tester
After=network-online.target
Wants=network-online.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=pi
WorkingDirectory=/home/pi/ISP_truth_tester
ExecStart=/home/pi/ISP_truth_tester/.venv/bin/isp-truth-tester run --duration 8
Restart=no

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

